WEBVTT

00:28.162 --> 00:29.762
    (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)     

00:37.805 --> 00:39.104
         (DOOR OPENING)         

00:39.840 --> 00:40.639
           (BANGING)            

00:41.942 --> 00:43.709
         (DOOR CLOSING)         

00:48.649 --> 00:50.783
      (SWITCHES FLICKING)       

00:53.754 --> 00:54.686
      (ENGINE SPUTTERING)       

00:57.758 --> 00:58.690
       (ENGINE STARTING)        

01:05.299 --> 01:06.665
     (AIRPLANE TAKING OFF)      

01:32.126 --> 01:33.425
        (BOMB WHISTLING)        

01:35.763 --> 01:37.162
          (EXPLOSION)           
  (NARRATOR SPEAKING SPANISH)   

01:37.164 --> 01:39.465
  The war for freedom continues 

01:39.467 --> 01:43.769
  whilst heroic deeds are done  
  throughout our territory.     

01:43.771 --> 01:48.974
   Our magnificent loyalist     
   militia have expelled        
   the fascists from Madrid.    

01:48.976 --> 01:54.746
   The defeated totalitarians   
   head north with the aid      
   of the enemies of freedom:   

01:54.748 --> 01:57.483
      the Italian fascists      
      and German Nazis,         

01:57.485 --> 02:00.686
     aiming to attack           
     the impenetrable           
     North Democratic Belt.     

02:00.688 --> 02:04.189
  From the Basque Country       
  barricades, tireless militia  
  will defend democracy,        

02:04.825 --> 02:07.192
    prepared to sweat blood.    

02:07.194 --> 02:09.794
     A frightened Franco        
     seeks help from Hitler     

02:09.797 --> 02:13.432
     and his Condor Legion,     
     led by Von Richthofen,     

02:13.434 --> 02:14.867
       cousin of the            
       Red Baron himself.       

02:17.104 --> 02:21.006
 To stop them, the Soviet Union 
 has sent their bravest         
 to fight for democracy         

02:21.008 --> 02:22.541
         (MAN COUGHING)         

02:22.543 --> 02:27.146
    on the battlefield          
    with a message of death     
    to the fascists.            

02:30.851 --> 02:35.387
     We will not allow          
     fascist fallacies          
     to poison our spirit.      

02:35.389 --> 02:37.055
  We won the battle in Madrid.  
  We shall win!                 

02:37.057 --> 02:37.689
 (MAN CLAPPING SLOWLY)          
                          Shh.  

02:38.826 --> 02:39.858
 HENRY: Really?                 

02:41.262 --> 02:42.494
                 (MAN SHUSHING) 

02:42.496 --> 02:45.130
 I despise propaganda, pal.     

02:45.132 --> 02:47.232
 I don't care                   
 who's slingin' it.             

02:52.306 --> 02:53.305
                       Comrade, 

02:55.376 --> 02:57.176
             may I have a swig? 

02:58.245 --> 02:59.678
   Sovietski?                   

02:59.680 --> 03:00.512
                           <i> Da.</i> 

03:01.482 --> 03:03.415
 Can't share it, pal.           

03:04.351 --> 03:06.952
 Cough syrup.                   
 Sore throat, see?              

03:07.755 --> 03:09.388
                    American.   

03:09.390 --> 03:10.923
            It is not your war. 

03:13.160 --> 03:14.426
         Right.                 

03:15.629 --> 03:17.963
 But I'm still here, anyway.    

04:13.187 --> 04:14.720
          MAN: Hello?           

04:14.722 --> 04:16.887
 Hello, Francois, how are you?  

04:16.890 --> 04:18.890
     Good, good.                
     Just arrived               
     a couple of days ago.      

04:18.892 --> 04:21.093
 Yes, getting in touch with     
 the city.                      

04:21.095 --> 04:23.862
     You know, you can't see    
     a single soldier here.     

04:25.065 --> 04:27.666
    No. I'm sure. I'm sure.     

04:27.668 --> 04:31.903
   Yes. No tanks, no weapons.   

04:31.905 --> 04:34.506
 <i> They're all in the border</i>     
 <i> trying to defend here, but...</i> 

04:34.508 --> 04:35.607
 <i> Yes, somebody told me. Yes...</i> 

04:36.477 --> 04:37.876
           Francois?            

04:39.913 --> 04:41.480
                    Hello?      

04:42.616 --> 04:43.482
             (SIGHS)            

04:45.019 --> 04:46.218
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

04:46.220 --> 04:49.655
 Hey, what are you doing?       
 I was transmitting my article. 

04:49.657 --> 04:51.590
 I work for a French newspaper. 

04:51.592 --> 04:54.092
       You know the rules.      

04:54.094 --> 04:58.797
        If you tell your paper  
        we're losing the war,   
        we cut you off.         

04:58.799 --> 05:01.500
          It's better than      
          canceling your permit 

05:01.502 --> 05:03.902
         or arresting you,      
         which we can also do.  

05:03.904 --> 05:06.138
   Please...                    

05:06.140 --> 05:10.575
 I'm just trying                
 to do my job.                  
           So am I.             

05:10.577 --> 05:13.879
   Carmen, I want a copy        
   of his articles one hour     
   before transmission.         

05:24.358 --> 05:25.657
      (SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE) 

05:25.659 --> 05:28.093
            It's the first time 
            he's been sent      
            as a journalist.    

05:29.630 --> 05:30.962
           How are you feeling? 

05:32.066 --> 05:33.498
       You don't look too good. 

05:35.002 --> 05:36.501
 I didn't sleep well.           

05:37.171 --> 05:38.704
 I've a lot on my mind.         

05:40.441 --> 05:43.342
       Vasyl is waiting for you 
       in his office. Go on.    

05:45.145 --> 05:46.945
   (CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)    

05:49.917 --> 05:51.416
       (KNOCKING ON DOOR)       
      Mmm.                      

05:53.854 --> 05:55.420
            Good morning.       

05:56.190 --> 05:58.390
 Teresa. How are you?           

05:58.392 --> 05:59.524
             Good.              

05:59.526 --> 06:00.692
     One moment.                

06:02.963 --> 06:04.930
               This is for you. 

06:04.932 --> 06:06.832
 Oh, no. You shouldn't.         

06:06.834 --> 06:07.966
      Well, I missed you. Come. 

06:10.437 --> 06:11.603
        How was Madrid?         

06:11.605 --> 06:13.505
               Well, dangerous. 

06:13.507 --> 06:15.440
       And I'm glad to be here. 

06:15.442 --> 06:17.209
             They're beautiful. 

06:17.211 --> 06:19.511
 Beauty attracts beauty.        

06:20.414 --> 06:21.713
 I forgot one more thing.       

06:24.418 --> 06:25.851
          Here you go.          

06:29.957 --> 06:31.123
 Too heavy                      
 for chocolates, huh?           

06:31.125 --> 06:31.990
                   It is.       

06:40.000 --> 06:41.833
 Oh, Vasyl...                   

06:41.835 --> 06:42.934
                Do you like it? 

06:43.904 --> 06:44.770
      Thank you.                

06:50.511 --> 06:52.177
   (INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)   

07:02.256 --> 07:03.488
 (MEN SHOUTING IN THE DISTANCE) 

07:05.826 --> 07:07.626
 (MEN SHOUTING IN SPANISH)      

07:07.628 --> 07:09.594
 You'll pay for it.             
 Hit him, hit him.              

07:14.001 --> 07:14.933
              (CAMERA CLICKING) 

07:17.504 --> 07:18.937
     (ALL SPEAKING SPANISH)     

07:18.939 --> 07:20.572
               What's going on? 
  He'll be hanged.              

07:20.574 --> 07:23.175
      He's lucky if that's all. 
       His plane was shot down. 

07:23.177 --> 07:25.577
          He's one of the       
          German bomber pilots. 

07:27.281 --> 07:28.480
            (GROANS)            

07:31.318 --> 07:32.951
     (LIVELY PIANO PLAYING)     

07:36.356 --> 07:37.489
      (MAN WOLF-WHISTLING)      

07:38.392 --> 07:40.125
    Hey, don't you dare!        

07:56.877 --> 07:57.809
            Oh.                 

07:58.979 --> 08:00.679
     Hey, Marta.                

08:00.681 --> 08:04.249
              Hey, Henry.       
              I've been waiting 
              for you outside.  

08:04.251 --> 08:06.184
               (MAN SHUSHING)   
 (TOASTS IN FRENCH)             

08:07.454 --> 08:08.620
          So, now you're drunk. 

08:09.156 --> 08:10.722
 Not drunk enough.              

08:11.525 --> 08:12.924
             Come on. Let's go. 

08:14.361 --> 08:15.727
         (BOY SPEAKING SPANISH) 

08:15.729 --> 08:19.498
                 Wait, sir!     
                 Wait! Do you   
                 want an apple? 

08:19.500 --> 08:20.832
              Oh.               

08:20.834 --> 08:22.300
             Sure.              

08:22.302 --> 08:23.201
             Uh...              

08:24.771 --> 08:25.704
       There you go.            
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

08:25.706 --> 08:27.839
           Thank you!           

08:27.841 --> 08:30.108
      Take a tip.               
      Never eat the local food. 

08:32.379 --> 08:34.880
 Come on. It takes              
 an hour to get to the front.   

08:35.649 --> 08:37.616
 Now, wait a minute, because... 

08:37.618 --> 08:41.052
  What do we want               
  to go to the battlefield for, 
  anyway, huh?                  

08:41.054 --> 08:42.888
           I got a better idea. 
           Look. Look.          

08:47.895 --> 08:49.427
               This morning's   
               troop movements. 

08:49.429 --> 08:50.662
     Where did you              
     get that map?              

08:51.632 --> 08:53.031
                     I drew it. 

08:53.033 --> 08:54.833
    You drew it?                

08:54.835 --> 08:58.003
   I figure we'd just,          
   you know, add a few details, 
   like, uh...                  

08:58.972 --> 09:00.972
  What?                         
                       My name. 

09:00.974 --> 09:02.173
    Uh-huh.                     

09:02.175 --> 09:03.508
                In big letters. 

09:03.510 --> 09:04.943
            And we take         
            a nice photo of it. 
            You know?           

09:04.945 --> 09:06.545
    There,                      
    in front of those sandbags. 

09:09.249 --> 09:11.249
                       Henry... 

09:11.251 --> 09:13.618
        What kind of journalist 
        have you turned into?   

09:14.288 --> 09:15.687
 A wise one.                    

09:18.992 --> 09:20.158
                         Henry! 

09:22.062 --> 09:24.029
                    Hey...      

09:24.031 --> 09:25.597
   Are you really going to      
   lie to your paper like that? 

09:25.599 --> 09:27.566
         No. Not a lie.         

09:27.568 --> 09:28.900
 It's the truth.                

09:29.570 --> 09:31.069
 I've seen war, Marta.          

09:31.071 --> 09:33.905
 I know the truth of war,       
 and I know how to tell it.     

09:33.907 --> 09:36.308
 So, the truth is               
 whatever I choose to write.    

09:36.310 --> 09:38.376
         Now...                 

09:38.378 --> 09:39.811
     Cheese.                    
                          No.   

09:39.813 --> 09:41.580
 You know you adore me.         
 Come on.                       

09:54.261 --> 09:54.993
       (CAMERA CLICKING)        

09:56.563 --> 09:58.163
    (CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING    
    ON GRAMOPHONE)              

10:01.768 --> 10:04.803
 Guess who has tickets          
 to the Bach                    
 concert next weekend?          

10:06.039 --> 10:06.938
        It's me.                

10:07.608 --> 10:08.940
    I pulled strings.           

10:08.942 --> 10:11.142
            I would love to go. 
         Good.                  

10:11.144 --> 10:12.844
             Bach is wonderful. 

10:12.846 --> 10:15.113
         Although               
         I prefer Shostakovich. 

10:15.115 --> 10:17.148
       But now the Soviets      
       have sent him to prison. 

10:17.150 --> 10:19.017
 Yes, but you know,             
 I don't support these methods. 

10:19.019 --> 10:21.119
            But I can           
            tease you, can't I? 

10:21.121 --> 10:23.088
    Of course.                  

10:25.125 --> 10:28.093
      Teresa,                   

10:28.095 --> 10:30.095
 if you and I were              
 together again, I...           
    (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)     

10:30.097 --> 10:31.162
                  Vasyl, I...   

10:32.265 --> 10:34.199
      Look here,                
      from the Danish reporter. 

10:34.201 --> 10:36.368
        She was trying to       
        smuggle this out.       

10:40.674 --> 10:42.574
             I'll deal with it. 

10:42.576 --> 10:44.275
    Thank you.                  

10:44.277 --> 10:45.143
                       Come on. 

11:03.430 --> 11:04.863
      MARTA: Poor people.       

11:11.104 --> 11:13.738
     Looks like fascists        
     are winning positions.     

11:22.382 --> 11:23.515
   (SOLDIER SPEAKING SPANISH)   
       (DISTANT GUNFIRE)        

11:23.517 --> 11:26.117
 They have snipers.             
 They've shot two of our men.   

11:27.454 --> 11:28.853
  We'll rescue them.            

11:28.855 --> 11:30.255
 Those two guys are history.    

11:35.595 --> 11:36.428
     (PLEADING IN SPANISH)      

11:39.566 --> 11:40.832
   (SOFTLY) This                
   fog is impossible.           

11:42.803 --> 11:43.902
            HENRY: Whoa, Marta. 
            Get back here.      

11:44.638 --> 11:46.838
                       (SCOFFS) 

11:46.840 --> 11:49.541
  Look, when I was in Ethiopia, 
  my interpreter tried          
  to do something brave.        

11:49.543 --> 11:52.277
        The newspaper           
        turned its back on him. 

11:52.279 --> 11:55.146
            He's in prison now. 
            They won't even     
            pay for his lawyer. 

11:55.148 --> 11:57.115
      What the hell do you      
      wanna risk your life for? 

11:57.117 --> 11:59.484
            Make the newspaper  
            owners even richer? 

12:01.688 --> 12:03.521
   Take the picture             
   that will turn               
   the world around.            

12:03.523 --> 12:05.356
                       (SCOFFS) 

12:05.358 --> 12:06.524
 Marta, no! Come back here!     
      (SOLDIER IN SPANISH)      

12:06.526 --> 12:07.892
 Come back here!                

12:07.894 --> 12:08.359
   HENRY:                       
   Are you out of your mind?    

12:11.231 --> 12:13.298
             Marta!             
   (SOLDIER SPEAKING SPANISH)   

12:13.300 --> 12:15.133
   Don't do that!               
   It's dangerous!              

12:15.135 --> 12:16.801
 Well, what about her?          
 She can't stay out there!      

12:16.803 --> 12:17.836
   Marta!                       

12:24.411 --> 12:25.510
  Marta, don't!                 

12:30.951 --> 12:31.916
      (SOLDIER 2 GROANING)      

12:32.919 --> 12:33.818
  (SOLDIER 2 SPEAKING SPANISH)  

12:33.820 --> 12:35.086
      Help me.                  

12:49.870 --> 12:50.869
           (GROANING)           

13:28.074 --> 13:30.208
        Shit. Shit. Shit. Shit. 

13:37.150 --> 13:38.183
  (SOLDIER 2 SPEAKING SPANISH)  

13:38.185 --> 13:39.417
                    Please.     

13:40.520 --> 13:41.953
                   Help!        

13:44.357 --> 13:45.523
 Do something.                  

13:54.334 --> 13:55.366
         (EARS RINGING)         

14:02.609 --> 14:03.575
         HENRY: Marta!          

14:04.311 --> 14:05.376
 Marta, leave it!               

14:08.481 --> 14:09.581
                       Go! Now! 

14:09.583 --> 14:10.415
         (GUNS FIRING)          

14:30.403 --> 14:31.502
             What the hell      
             were you thinking? 

14:31.504 --> 14:33.338
 I don't know.                  
 What were you thinking?        

14:33.340 --> 14:34.472
                 (PANTING)      

14:36.743 --> 14:37.876
      (GUNFIRE CONTINUES)       

14:39.880 --> 14:41.212
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

14:41.214 --> 14:43.214
 That picture is important.     
 Publish it.                    

15:03.603 --> 15:05.169
 I put some brandy in it.       

15:06.473 --> 15:07.505
            Thank you.          

15:10.610 --> 15:12.577
    Please. Eat.                

15:13.446 --> 15:14.979
             Thank you so much. 

15:20.687 --> 15:21.920
 Pretty good, huh?              
                    Mmm-hmm.    

15:28.662 --> 15:29.527
       You don't want anything? 

15:29.529 --> 15:30.428
         <i> Nyet.</i>                 

15:36.303 --> 15:37.535
 HENRY: Why don't you           
 become a fashion photographer? 

15:38.505 --> 15:40.405
    Or sports?                  

15:41.374 --> 15:43.074
                I want my Capa. 

15:43.076 --> 15:45.276
 Robert Capa is overrated.      

15:45.278 --> 15:47.312
                 Hemingway,     
                 too, isn't he? 

15:47.314 --> 15:49.447
        Everybody is overrated, 
        but not you.            

15:49.449 --> 15:50.882
 I didn't say that.             

15:50.884 --> 15:53.418
 You've had your glory moments. 
 Now leave room for us.         

15:58.325 --> 16:00.058
   (AIRPLANE FLYING OVERHEAD)   

16:00.060 --> 16:01.559
           Wow. That was close. 

16:01.561 --> 16:02.627
                    German?     

16:11.671 --> 16:12.971
              It's coming back. 

16:12.973 --> 16:13.705
      (BRAKES SCREECHING)       

16:16.676 --> 16:17.442
       HENRY: Go, go, go!       

16:21.514 --> 16:22.880
        The papers! The camera! 

16:22.882 --> 16:23.681
           No, wait!            

16:27.620 --> 16:28.619
            (BOTH GROANING)     

16:38.164 --> 16:39.163
                    Shit.       
          Ow!                   

16:40.000 --> 16:41.099
         Ow!                    

16:42.969 --> 16:44.202
                  You okay?     
      Yeah.                     

16:45.739 --> 16:47.171
 Stupid picture!                

16:56.583 --> 16:58.616
     (INDISTINCT                
     ANNOUNCEMENT OVER PA)      

17:23.910 --> 17:25.042
 MARCO: ...something like that. 

17:25.045 --> 17:26.176
 Hey, Henry.                    

17:27.446 --> 17:28.279
   Wow.                         

17:28.815 --> 17:30.815
                   Marco.       

17:30.817 --> 17:32.884
                I wondered when 
                you'd show up.  

17:32.886 --> 17:34.619
              Like a bad penny. 

17:34.621 --> 17:36.921
 Yes. (LAUGHS)                  

17:36.923 --> 17:39.757
 I heard your car               
 was bombed.                    

17:39.759 --> 17:44.929
 But I thought it was you       
 telling your usual stories,    
 but now...                     

17:44.931 --> 17:46.330
         (WHISPERING) And I     
         heard that you've been 
         secretly writing       

17:46.332 --> 17:48.266
     articles for the fascists. 

17:49.769 --> 17:50.668
               Yes.             

17:52.205 --> 17:54.005
      It's dangerous            
      when you cross the lines, 
      Marco.                    

17:54.007 --> 17:55.306
    Mmm-hmm.                    

17:55.308 --> 17:57.341
         You get yourself shot. 

17:57.343 --> 18:00.178
 If you write what they want,   
 you never get shot.            

18:01.347 --> 18:02.246
            (SIGHS)             

18:07.487 --> 18:08.986
 Didn't know you were here.     

18:08.988 --> 18:10.288
                    Hey, Marta. 

18:14.194 --> 18:15.927
 I'm so glad to see you again.  

18:15.929 --> 18:16.794
  MARTA: Glad to see you, too.  

18:22.168 --> 18:23.534
               George!          

18:24.204 --> 18:26.104
          How's New York?       

18:26.106 --> 18:27.772
       Where is my check?       

18:27.774 --> 18:30.608
 GEORGE: <i> Henry, we have</i>        
<i> cheaper journalists, you know.</i> 

18:30.610 --> 18:32.877
     Yeah, but none of them     
     is named Henry Howell.     

18:32.879 --> 18:35.546
    <i> They'll have</i>               
    <i> names of their own</i>         
    <i> if I give them a chance.</i>   

18:35.548 --> 18:37.982
   <i> Listen,</i>                     
   <i> child star Shirley Temple</i>   

18:37.984 --> 18:40.451
   <i> released a toy</i>              
   <i> collection with her face.</i>   

18:40.453 --> 18:42.253
       <i> And all the papers</i>      
       <i> opened with that.</i>       

18:42.255 --> 18:43.955
   <i> There's a war on, Henry...</i>  
     All right.                 
     Here's what we can do.     

18:43.957 --> 18:46.390
    I've got                    
    a hand-drawn battle map.    

18:46.392 --> 18:48.926
   Make a great illustration.   
   But...                       

18:48.928 --> 18:51.696
   Speaking of illustrations,   

18:51.698 --> 18:54.332
       how about a week         
       in Paris, George?        

18:54.334 --> 18:57.702
  Picasso is                    
  preparing a new exhibition.   

18:57.704 --> 18:58.736
       Let's do Picasso.        
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

18:58.738 --> 19:00.271
             Together.          

19:01.241 --> 19:02.440
  He'll talk to me, you know.   

19:02.442 --> 19:04.475
      <i> Nothing about Paris.</i>     

19:04.477 --> 19:07.245
 <i> Bergara.</i>                      
 <i> Do you remember that article?</i> 

19:07.247 --> 19:09.046
     <i> That's war.</i>               
     <i> And war sells, Henry.</i>     

19:09.048 --> 19:10.581
        <i> I want war! I...</i>       

19:46.119 --> 19:48.252
       (EAGLE SCREECHING)       

19:53.560 --> 19:54.825
       (SPEAKING GERMAN)        

19:54.827 --> 19:56.394
      Absolute perfection.      

20:03.736 --> 20:04.769
        (KNOCK ON DOOR)         

20:04.771 --> 20:05.670
            Come in.            

20:06.773 --> 20:07.638
                 Teresa?        

20:08.942 --> 20:10.841
 These are the new journalists. 

20:11.978 --> 20:16.113
        Marco Navas.            
        He works for            
        a Portuguese newspaper. 

20:16.115 --> 20:18.883
 And these two are the ones     
 with the car that broke down.  

20:18.885 --> 20:21.152
  No, it didn't break down.     
  It was bombed.                

20:21.154 --> 20:24.355
 Marta Vonier,                  
 photographer                   
 from <i> Le Figaro.</i>               

20:24.357 --> 20:28.793
 And Henry Howell,              
 from the <i> New York</i>             
 <i> Herald Tribune.</i> American.     

20:28.795 --> 20:31.062
       I studied your           
       writing at college. I... 

20:31.064 --> 20:32.663
 I think I've read it all.      

20:33.233 --> 20:35.233
        Short. Sharp.           

20:35.835 --> 20:36.834
 Very inspiring.                

20:38.004 --> 20:40.438
     Your style has evolved     
     over time, hasn't it?      

20:41.741 --> 20:45.009
 HENRY: Well,                   
 I'm still a growing boy.       

20:45.011 --> 20:46.844
           (TERESA CHUCKLES)    

20:46.846 --> 20:50.548
      I just read this article  
      of yours about Bergara.   

20:50.550 --> 20:53.551
           You write of         
           a battle at a castle 

20:53.553 --> 20:57.388
            where our soldiers  
            were firing from    
            the battlements.    

20:58.992 --> 21:00.258
      I think it was            
      a pretty good piece.      

21:02.862 --> 21:06.564
         It's quite interesting 
         because there are      
         no castles in Bergara. 

21:07.467 --> 21:10.268
     Why? Why did you write it? 

21:10.270 --> 21:12.336
            Is it even about    
            the truth anymore?  

21:13.706 --> 21:17.675
  Well, maybe I got             
  the name of the town wrong.   

21:18.144 --> 21:19.844
        There's so many.        

21:19.846 --> 21:22.647
            Don't play with us. 

21:22.649 --> 21:25.650
         For you, it's a story. 
         But for us,            
         it's life and death.   

21:25.652 --> 21:27.652
 VASYL: Obey the rules,         
 Mr. Howell.                    

21:28.621 --> 21:30.721
    They're simple              
    enough even for you.        

21:31.557 --> 21:33.424
      I'm sorry. You are?       

21:36.729 --> 21:37.595
  Mmm...                        

21:39.365 --> 21:40.898
 We've got                      
 a question.                    

21:42.568 --> 21:45.169
             We lost everything 
             in the explosion.  

21:45.171 --> 21:47.538
 So, we need new papers.        

21:48.675 --> 21:50.308
     We will let you            
     know your status.          

21:50.310 --> 21:52.410
          And you have to wait. 

21:52.412 --> 21:55.112
  In the meantime,              
  we can provide you            
  with a camera and some films, 

21:55.114 --> 21:56.747
 so you can continue your work. 

21:58.117 --> 22:01.385
    But the freedom of movement 
    is restricted in this area. 

22:01.387 --> 22:02.586
     Stay away from the border. 

22:03.089 --> 22:04.422
                 So, please...  

22:04.424 --> 22:05.856
             (SPEAKING SPANISH) 

22:05.858 --> 22:06.924
          Thank you.            

22:08.861 --> 22:10.561
          Here it is.           

22:13.099 --> 22:14.832
   That's all we have.          

22:23.242 --> 22:24.375
   (INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)   

22:36.122 --> 22:37.555
   (CAPTAIN SPEAKING GERMAN)    
        (MUSIC PLAYING)         

22:37.557 --> 22:39.857
         Gentlemen,             
         your results!          

22:39.859 --> 22:43.427
 Thomas is first with 16 hits,  
 Matthias is second with 12     

22:43.429 --> 22:45.730
   and Wolfgang                 
   is third with 9.             

22:45.732 --> 22:51.168
     So this week's bonus       
     is for Thomas Selber.      

22:51.170 --> 22:53.804
              Are you saving up 
              for the wedding   
              or a house?       

22:53.806 --> 22:57.441
          No, I came here       
          to buy this truck.    

22:57.443 --> 23:00.544
       These Spanish girls      
       would be cheaper.        
       Attention!               

23:02.548 --> 23:03.714
         (MUSIC STOPS)          

23:06.519 --> 23:09.120
 Lieutenant Colonel             
 Von Richthofen!                

23:09.122 --> 23:10.154
          Stand to attention!   

23:12.558 --> 23:18.896
     Discipline.                
     Gentlemen, discipline!     

23:18.898 --> 23:22.600
      We have lost men          
      through pilot error.      

23:24.303 --> 23:28.105
  One was saved                 
  by his parachute,             
  but he was taken to Bilbao.   

23:29.575 --> 23:32.410
       Two others died          
       in a car accident        

23:32.412 --> 23:36.147
   coming back                  
   from one of those parties.   

23:37.183 --> 23:38.582
          Don't forget,         

23:39.285 --> 23:42.286
     we lost the Great War      

23:42.288 --> 23:45.790
       but today might be       
       our second chance.       

23:46.325 --> 23:47.758
                (STEAM HISSING) 

23:52.632 --> 23:54.031
 Don't take it too hard.        

23:55.968 --> 23:57.968
      Well,                     
      she's just doing her job. 

23:59.038 --> 24:00.204
      I'm just doing mine.      

24:00.740 --> 24:01.772
         Yeah.                  

24:02.875 --> 24:05.009
        This old piece of junk. 
        (CAR ENGINE SPUTTERING) 

24:05.011 --> 24:07.144
                   I can't work 
                   with this.   

24:07.146 --> 24:09.613
               Are you crossing 
               the lines again? 

24:09.615 --> 24:12.016
                Don't you need  
                a photographer? 

24:12.018 --> 24:15.052
 Are you offering yourself      
 to the fascists, Marta?        

24:20.426 --> 24:22.126
    Or to me?                   

24:22.128 --> 24:23.294
 MAN: Hey, you're American?     

24:23.296 --> 24:24.495
             (SPEAKING SPANISH) 

24:24.497 --> 24:25.596
                      Yes.      

24:26.699 --> 24:29.066
  They sold me a car.           
  It's not good.                

24:29.068 --> 24:31.001
 All Yanks know how to          
 fix cars, don't you?           

24:32.572 --> 24:34.071
        I don't do auto repair. 

24:37.210 --> 24:38.476
       Okay.                    

24:39.278 --> 24:40.144
     Thank you.                 

24:41.481 --> 24:42.513
   Hey!                         
                         <i> Si?</i>   

24:42.515 --> 24:43.747
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

24:43.749 --> 24:45.683
    Does anyone know            
    how to fix a car?           
                    Yes.        

25:01.100 --> 25:03.200
    He gets under your skin,    
    this Mr. Howell?            

25:03.669 --> 25:06.270
    No, not really.             

25:06.272 --> 25:08.072
    I suppose he's charismatic. 

25:08.074 --> 25:08.939
 TERESA: Well,                  

25:10.643 --> 25:11.609
 this is undeniable.            

25:13.212 --> 25:15.479
         But is he on our side? 

25:15.481 --> 25:17.181
 He's on nobody's side.         

25:18.217 --> 25:21.051
 Look, he made a mistake.       

25:21.053 --> 25:24.054
 But he can                     
 still be useful to us          
 with Americans.                

25:25.358 --> 25:28.259
           Americans don't care 
           about anything.      

25:28.261 --> 25:29.727
                  Don't forget. 

25:37.336 --> 25:39.003
     (CAR ENGINE STARTING)      

25:42.942 --> 25:44.241
   Here you are, Mr. Howell.    
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

25:44.243 --> 25:45.843
        Thank you, Nicolie.     

25:51.717 --> 25:54.285
     PIERRE: Henry! Henry?      

25:55.388 --> 25:57.354
            Pierre.             

25:57.356 --> 25:58.856
                       Pierre.  

25:58.858 --> 25:59.924
      Still in the white suits. 

25:59.926 --> 26:01.191
             Yes.               

26:01.193 --> 26:03.193
 When was the last time?        

26:03.195 --> 26:04.562
                Chaco War, '32. 

26:04.564 --> 26:05.930
         Oh, yes.               

26:06.899 --> 26:09.633
  How is Spain looking to you?  

26:09.635 --> 26:11.268
                    It's worse. 
      (SPEAKING FRENCH)         

26:11.270 --> 26:12.503
            Exactly.            

26:12.505 --> 26:14.104
     It's fantastic for us.     

26:14.106 --> 26:15.739
                         Great. 

26:15.741 --> 26:18.342
          I'm told we can get   
          the best photographs. 

26:18.344 --> 26:20.110
           Would you excuse me? 

26:21.080 --> 26:22.313
      Who is that?              

26:24.483 --> 26:26.984
  A literary genius, so called. 

26:26.986 --> 26:29.887
            Wrote a book about  
            some Negro soldiers 

26:29.889 --> 26:32.289
           who fought in France 
           in The Great War.    

26:32.291 --> 26:34.191
 The Harlem Hellfighters?       

26:34.193 --> 26:36.226
 Is that                        
 the famous Henry Howell?       

26:44.437 --> 26:45.869
  Room service.                 

26:50.009 --> 26:51.675
      Marta?                    

26:56.782 --> 26:59.850
 Look, I've been asking around, 

27:00.920 --> 27:03.320
 and I found you a Leica.       

27:03.322 --> 27:05.823
 It's going to do               
 what you're looking for.       

27:05.825 --> 27:07.825
 It's got a real                
 high-speed lens on it.         

27:08.728 --> 27:10.160
 It'll get you a Capa.          

27:13.666 --> 27:15.099
     Marta?                     

27:26.912 --> 27:28.679
 MARTA: (WHISPERING)            
 Do you think he heard us?      

27:28.681 --> 27:30.047
 (INDISTINCT WHISPERING)        

27:38.357 --> 27:42.126
  Vasyl.                        
  The Consul is waiting for you 
  in your office.               

27:47.066 --> 27:48.799
   CONSUL: Take the profiles    
   of the journalists.          

27:53.372 --> 27:54.738
           I didn't expect you, 
           Mr. Consul.          

27:56.742 --> 27:59.943
 We will return                 
 these files.                   

27:59.945 --> 28:02.146
          Might I have a moment 
          to discuss something  
          of a personal nature? 

28:03.282 --> 28:05.182
 CONSUL: Are you                
 referring to your brother?     

28:05.184 --> 28:06.216
              Yes, sir.         

28:09.088 --> 28:10.254
        Come.                   

28:12.758 --> 28:14.925
 Your brother will              
 find that Siberia              

28:14.927 --> 28:17.728
          becomes more gentle   
          at this time of year. 

28:17.730 --> 28:19.363
   He's a poet.                 

28:19.365 --> 28:21.098
 Poets sometimes write          
 things they're sorry for.      

28:21.100 --> 28:22.966
              Comrade Stalin    
              has not forgotten 

28:22.968 --> 28:24.668
          that you were         
          with the Trotskyites, 

28:24.670 --> 28:28.072
        and that you publicly   
        expressed your remorse. 
        But Nikolai...          

28:28.074 --> 28:30.207
   No. Please, sir. Wait, wait. 

28:31.477 --> 28:33.744
                Nikolai doesn't 
                deserve this.   

28:34.914 --> 28:37.047
 Do you want to solve this?     
                      Yes.      

28:38.417 --> 28:43.287
 Perhaps you could bring me     
 an enemy of the revolution.    

28:43.289 --> 28:45.322
 Find this person,              

28:45.324 --> 28:48.092
 and I will find                
 a crime to fit him with.       

29:11.951 --> 29:13.317
  WOMAN: Thank you very much.   

29:18.524 --> 29:19.957
                    Mr. Howell. 

29:19.959 --> 29:21.425
   Hi, Maria.                   

29:22.394 --> 29:25.095
     Look, I, um...             

29:25.097 --> 29:28.465
 I need to get                  
 something out of the country   
 without the censors seeing it. 

29:28.467 --> 29:29.967
                         Ah.    

29:29.969 --> 29:31.735
 I heard you could fix that.    

29:31.737 --> 29:35.305
   Sure... But it is expensive. 

29:35.307 --> 29:38.709
 Okay. So, charge it            
 to Marco's room.               

29:38.711 --> 29:39.476
 And prepare my bags            
 for checkout.                  

29:40.112 --> 29:41.044
               Are you leaving? 

29:41.714 --> 29:43.447
     Paris.                     

29:43.449 --> 29:44.681
          You are not           
          staying for the tour? 

29:44.683 --> 29:46.150
       Tour?                    

29:46.152 --> 29:48.018
    Yes, the Press Office tour. 

29:48.020 --> 29:50.254
 No, I'm not staying for        
 the Press Office tour.         

29:51.223 --> 29:52.823
                Hey, Henry.     

29:53.959 --> 29:54.858
               Are you running  
               away again?      

29:56.595 --> 29:58.061
 MARTA: Come on!                

29:58.063 --> 29:59.329
 They're buying us lunch.       
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

29:59.331 --> 30:00.864
                   Come on.     

30:00.866 --> 30:02.800
            MARIA: Don't worry. 
            I have the right    
            connections.        

30:02.802 --> 30:04.601
 I should give it to you now?   
 Or...                          

30:04.603 --> 30:06.270
                       Uh, yes. 

30:08.174 --> 30:11.041
    Mr. Howell, are you sending 
    some of your                
    fiction to New York?        

30:13.145 --> 30:15.879
        No, no. It's            
        a birthday card.        
        Grandmother.            

30:16.949 --> 30:18.782
    Fancy a little sightseeing? 

30:18.784 --> 30:20.184
            I...                

30:22.755 --> 30:25.889
    Please.                     
    You will be our star guest. 

30:28.828 --> 30:30.227
               I'm on my knees. 

30:49.715 --> 30:50.414
 VASYL: What is he doing here?  

30:51.450 --> 30:52.850
                Calm down.      
                I invited him.  

30:52.852 --> 30:54.318
  I don't trust him.            

30:54.320 --> 30:56.253
            These people        
            work for newspapers 

30:56.255 --> 30:58.622
     that sell millions of      
     copies all over the world. 

30:58.624 --> 30:59.723
     We should look after them. 

30:59.725 --> 31:01.291
              No.               

31:01.293 --> 31:04.261
       Please, Vasyl.           
       I know how to do my job. 

31:04.263 --> 31:05.796
      Please come with me.      
      My brother, he's...       

31:05.798 --> 31:09.132
 I thought                      
 the great Communist Party      
 was obsessed with schedules.   

31:09.134 --> 31:10.467
 We wouldn't                    
 wanna be late.                 

31:13.505 --> 31:15.038
            Let's talk later.   
       (SPEAKING RUSSIAN)       

31:15.040 --> 31:16.240
              Thank you.        

31:19.879 --> 31:21.044
 (BOTH SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE) 

31:21.046 --> 31:22.412
         Where's the journalist 
         from Madrid?           

31:22.414 --> 31:24.748
          No idea,              
          he's always late.     

31:24.750 --> 31:25.983
               Let's go.        

31:57.783 --> 32:00.217
           CARMEN: You have one 
           hour to take photos. 

32:00.219 --> 32:02.753
 Enjoy the food, the views,     

32:02.755 --> 32:06.757
 and write nice things about us 
 if you can, okay?              

32:06.759 --> 32:10.160
      If somebody wants         
      to go to the top,         
      there are 241 steps.      

32:11.163 --> 32:13.664
 Good luck.                     
 The views are amazing.         

32:13.666 --> 32:15.098
 We meet back at the bus.       

32:29.148 --> 32:30.280
   (SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE)    

32:30.282 --> 32:31.415
      I'll come up shortly.     

32:36.989 --> 32:38.522
             Are you coming up? 

32:41.894 --> 32:43.327
  Absolutely beautiful.         

32:44.563 --> 32:45.696
                    Yes, it is. 

32:48.600 --> 32:50.701
 You wanna start over?          

32:51.837 --> 32:53.070
                     Why not?   

32:56.542 --> 32:57.407
                     Bit early. 

32:58.877 --> 33:00.243
     More for me.               

33:02.681 --> 33:04.581
 All right. You just live once. 

33:05.851 --> 33:06.750
      There you go.             

33:15.294 --> 33:16.693
  So, what's your               
  life's story?                 

33:18.130 --> 33:19.730
       I wanted to be a writer. 

33:21.100 --> 33:23.100
     But when the war happened, 

33:23.102 --> 33:26.503
    the loyalists needed people 
    who spoke languages,        

33:26.505 --> 33:28.839
         and knew how to        
         deal with journalists. 

33:28.841 --> 33:31.108
 Ah. So you're dealing with me? 

33:31.110 --> 33:32.509
               Well, in my way. 

33:34.046 --> 33:37.147
 And because you                
 didn't become a writer,        

33:37.149 --> 33:39.516
 you deal in editing            
 what other people write.       

33:39.518 --> 33:43.353
         Well, circumstances    
         delimit one's choices, 
         don't they?            

33:45.624 --> 33:48.792
                  To be honest, 
                  I'm like you. 

33:50.262 --> 33:52.262
                I don't fit in  
                many places.    

33:56.268 --> 33:58.368
 You're a Communist?            

33:58.370 --> 34:00.570
                    Loyalist.   

34:00.572 --> 34:02.572
         I wish to see          
         a democracy for Spain. 

34:24.096 --> 34:25.295
     (BOTH SPEAKING GERMAN)     

34:25.297 --> 34:28.098
         Morning,               
         my Lieutenant Colonel. 

34:28.100 --> 34:29.666
   Good morning,                
   Wolfgang.                    

34:29.668 --> 34:32.569
            Berlin wants        
            better air and land 
            coordination.       

34:32.571 --> 34:36.440
           With the Spanish?    
           Impossible.          

34:36.442 --> 34:38.408
          The engine is fine    
          but check piston two. 

34:40.646 --> 34:43.380
       The Spanish aren't       
       the only ones, Wolfgang. 

34:43.382 --> 34:47.417
        The Italians are pretty 
        much the same.          

34:47.418 --> 34:50.520
 We learn something             
 new every day.                 

34:50.522 --> 34:55.257
        Meanwhile our men       
        are holding out against 
        syphilis and diarrhea.  

34:55.260 --> 35:00.397
 Minister Goring wants          
 to bomb a city as a birthday   
 present to Hitler.             

35:00.399 --> 35:02.966
        Fine. It's a nice       
        present for our Fuhrer. 

35:02.968 --> 35:05.602
           He will see what     
           the German Air Force 
           is capable of.       

35:07.439 --> 35:09.706
       HENRY: Hey, what's that? 
       Revolutionary pin?       

35:10.375 --> 35:11.308
        No.                     

35:12.511 --> 35:16.847
 It's a football pin.           
 Athletic club.                 

35:16.849 --> 35:18.615
 From Bilbao, my city.          

35:20.419 --> 35:23.587
 I wear it because              
 my father gave it to me        
 when he played for them.       

35:24.690 --> 35:26.256
              What's he do now? 

35:29.194 --> 35:30.594
  He passed away.               

35:33.499 --> 35:34.631
                     I'm sorry. 

35:37.903 --> 35:39.436
             You must miss him. 

35:40.239 --> 35:43.373
   Yes. Yes, I do.              

35:46.578 --> 35:48.778
  I wasn't a daughter           
  that he hoped for.            

35:50.549 --> 35:53.183
 He arranged my marriage        
 to a family friend,            

35:54.253 --> 35:55.652
      and I ran away.           

36:00.659 --> 36:03.393
 Here, in this country,         
 a lot of people believe        

36:03.395 --> 36:06.796
 that women can't               
 have their own opinions.       

36:09.468 --> 36:11.334
               CARMEN: Come on. 

36:11.336 --> 36:12.903
  Everybody to the bus, please. 

36:15.007 --> 36:16.940
       Let's go.                

36:16.942 --> 36:19.376
      CARMEN: <i> Next up,</i>         
     <i> a government hospital.</i>    

36:19.378 --> 36:22.479
      Supplies are              
      generously provided       
      by the Soviet Union.      

36:26.485 --> 36:28.885
     You have to talk to        
     your paper. I mean it.     

36:45.837 --> 36:47.003
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

36:47.005 --> 36:48.572
                  Hello.        
       Hello.                   

36:52.878 --> 36:53.843
                       Hi.      

36:58.350 --> 36:59.382
         Your cow needs a tail. 

37:02.988 --> 37:04.254
           How did this happen? 

37:05.457 --> 37:06.856
      Was it from the fighting? 

37:09.027 --> 37:12.762
          Better story for you  
          if I said yes, huh?   

37:12.764 --> 37:17.434
 I'll get the truth for you,    
 but the real truth             
 is on her face,                

37:17.436 --> 37:19.569
    no matter what              
    happened to her.            

37:20.472 --> 37:21.972
          She needs your help.  

37:26.979 --> 37:28.044
       (CAMERA CLICKING)        

37:28.046 --> 37:29.746
 Marta, please.                 

37:30.949 --> 37:32.315
    Thank you.                  

37:40.459 --> 37:42.125
      PIERRE: No, no, no.       
      The government            

37:42.127 --> 37:44.327
    is dead but                 
    behaves as if it isn't.     

37:45.764 --> 37:47.897
            The Basque front is 
            about to collapse.  

37:50.869 --> 37:53.069
           The thing is,        
           the retreat may come 

37:53.071 --> 37:55.205
       right through my         
       position here in Bilbao, 

37:55.207 --> 37:56.539
              by Gernika. So... 

37:58.410 --> 37:59.409
         (SPEAKING FRENCH)      

37:59.411 --> 38:01.011
                      Shit!     

38:01.013 --> 38:03.179
           What?                
           You know the rules.  

38:03.181 --> 38:04.514
       You are all such cynics. 

38:04.516 --> 38:06.249
 You have something for me?     

38:06.251 --> 38:07.384
                     Yeah.      
 (BOTH SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE) 

38:07.386 --> 38:08.985
            You'd better        
            go home, it's late. 

38:08.987 --> 38:11.488
    Right away.                 
    See you tomorrow.           

38:13.358 --> 38:16.493
             We have a report   
             that a journalist  
             has been in Burgos 

38:16.495 --> 38:18.161
            and now moves       
            freely in our area. 

38:18.163 --> 38:20.030
             Name?              
                    Not yet.    

38:20.032 --> 38:21.031
          Not acceptable.       

39:12.317 --> 39:13.650
           (TYPING)             
        (PIANO PLAYING)         

39:26.932 --> 39:28.098
     PIERRE: It isn't good?     

39:30.836 --> 39:33.636
                 No, it's shit. 

39:34.840 --> 39:36.139
      Dig deeper.               

39:41.179 --> 39:42.645
    My young lady found it.     

39:43.548 --> 39:45.448
 Bookstore. Just on the street. 

39:46.318 --> 39:48.418
 Antique bookstore, but...      

39:49.254 --> 39:50.787
        You want me to sign it? 

39:52.023 --> 39:52.989
 Keep it.                       

39:54.226 --> 39:55.925
 In fact, read it.              

40:09.341 --> 40:10.907
  (BASQUE FOLK MUSIC PLAYING)   

40:28.560 --> 40:29.893
       (CAMERA CLICKING)        

41:15.207 --> 41:18.641
     This is a Tree of Gernika. 

41:18.643 --> 41:22.045
            An ancient symbol   
            of Basque identity. 

41:22.047 --> 41:24.180
           Oak trees symbolized 
           traditional freedoms 

41:24.182 --> 41:27.150
         for Bizcayans and      
         for the Basque people. 

41:27.152 --> 41:31.354
          Many centuries ago,   
          under this tree,      
          laws were enacted,    

41:31.356 --> 41:35.959
        prohibiting torture     
        and arresting people    
        without court approval. 

41:35.961 --> 41:38.695
    You have five minutes       
    to take photos, okay?       
    We'll meet back at the bus. 

41:45.403 --> 41:47.837
    This is off the record,     

41:47.839 --> 41:50.240
    but do you wanna taste      
    the real Basque country?    

41:50.242 --> 41:51.875
          Wonderful...          

41:54.513 --> 41:55.945
                 Let's do it.   
          Let's do it.          

41:55.947 --> 41:58.414
   Teresa, where are you going? 

41:58.416 --> 42:01.117
 I'm gonna take them somewhere. 

42:01.119 --> 42:02.352
   Can you wait for me          
   in the front door, please?   

42:02.354 --> 42:03.653
             Sure.              

42:03.655 --> 42:04.988
       Give me a second.        

42:04.990 --> 42:06.489
 (BOTH SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE) 

42:06.491 --> 42:08.258
                They must stay  
                with the group. 

42:09.761 --> 42:12.529
               And you'd better 
               be careful.      

42:12.531 --> 42:13.730
           I owe you one.       

42:30.515 --> 42:31.648
     (MAN SPEAKING SPANISH)     

42:31.650 --> 42:33.483
              Why are you here? 

42:33.485 --> 42:35.618
            You know            
            you're not welcome. 

42:36.588 --> 42:37.987
                       Go away! 

42:37.989 --> 42:39.889
 Are you driving us out?        
 You?                           

42:41.826 --> 42:43.560
  When my son returns,          

42:43.562 --> 42:46.129
 you'll be the one              
 to be driven out!              

42:46.131 --> 42:50.300
         We all know which side 
         your son fights on.    
         On the fascists' side! 

42:51.069 --> 42:52.635
                      Leave it! 

42:52.637 --> 42:54.837
     I won't sell you anything. 
     No beetroots,              

42:54.839 --> 42:56.773
          no leeks, no carrots, 

42:56.775 --> 42:58.241
               no cauliflowers. 
               Nothing!         

42:58.243 --> 43:00.677
 You'll change your mind        
 when ours come along,          

43:01.279 --> 43:02.879
            when it's too late! 

43:02.881 --> 43:04.213
                  Are you sure? 
 Come on.                       

43:10.355 --> 43:11.721
  What's all that about then?   

43:11.723 --> 43:15.725
 Well,                          
 she supports the other side.   

43:15.727 --> 43:17.527
 Here, everybody knows          
 everything about everyone.     

43:17.529 --> 43:18.928
                Yeah?           

43:20.332 --> 43:21.698
     (CAR ENGINE STARTING)      

43:31.843 --> 43:33.509
        (VON RICHTHOFEN         
        SPEAKING GERMAN)        

43:33.511 --> 43:36.279
           We are 35 kilometers 
           away from the front. 

43:37.716 --> 43:40.650
         It's about to break.   

43:40.652 --> 43:44.120
   The Spanish have asked us    
   to attack with full force.   

43:45.790 --> 43:49.525
      They will retreat through 
      the mountains,            
      along that road.          

43:49.527 --> 43:51.728
             Franco wants       
             to stop them here. 

43:51.730 --> 43:55.732
     He'd better make sure      
     we get the ammo and        
     the fuel we were promised. 

43:55.734 --> 43:58.868
            They must make sure 
            our bills are paid. 

43:58.870 --> 44:01.771
             I've spoken        
             with General Mola. 

44:01.773 --> 44:05.975
          He wants us           
          to bomb all of        
          the Basque factories. 

44:05.977 --> 44:08.645
 Really?                        
 His own factories?             

44:08.647 --> 44:10.813
        The Spanish don't think 
        about the future.       

44:12.017 --> 44:14.150
          Soon there will be    
          no tomorrow for them. 

44:25.897 --> 44:27.063
          (GLASS SHATTERING)    

44:29.067 --> 44:30.266
       VASYL: What is going on? 

44:33.338 --> 44:37.407
  We stopped his car.           
  He was about to               
  cross enemy lines.            

44:38.877 --> 44:42.145
    I took the wrong road.      

44:42.147 --> 44:43.913
      They pulled out all       
      the traffic signs.        

44:45.450 --> 44:46.549
   Are you a spy?               

44:46.551 --> 44:49.152
          No!                   

44:49.154 --> 44:52.555
   No, for God's sake,          
   I don't know the area.       

44:52.557 --> 44:54.791
         I just...              

44:54.793 --> 44:56.759
   I just wanted to meet        
   with the journalist tour.    

44:58.463 --> 45:00.263
 Vasyl, I'm watching you.       

45:02.400 --> 45:03.766
 Show me what you can do.       

45:04.936 --> 45:06.002
      JOURNALIST: Please.       

45:07.238 --> 45:08.771
   Please, sir.                 
   I have two children.         

45:10.108 --> 45:11.407
                Have mercy.     

45:13.912 --> 45:15.211
          Have mercy.           

45:37.035 --> 45:38.034
        (WOMAN SPEAKING         
        OTHER LANGUAGE)         

45:38.036 --> 45:41.404
 Teresa! What a joy!            

45:42.974 --> 45:44.407
 It's been so long.             

45:50.281 --> 45:52.148
 This is Begona,                
 my mother's sister.            

45:52.150 --> 45:53.583
 The Coloma family              
 isn't as stuck up              

45:53.585 --> 45:54.217
 as my father's one.            
   (BEGONA IN OTHER LANGUAGE)   

45:54.619 --> 45:55.852
                     Nice girl! 

45:57.122 --> 45:59.989
 This is Henry,                 
 Marco and Marta.               

45:59.991 --> 46:02.358
 Foreign reporters.             
           Welcome.             

46:03.595 --> 46:05.728
            Look at you,        
            you look exhausted. 

46:05.730 --> 46:07.096
      Auntie...                 

46:07.699 --> 46:09.432
             She doesn't sleep. 

46:09.434 --> 46:12.702
            She's too sensitive 
            for this job.       
 Stop it.                       

46:12.704 --> 46:14.904
 It's none of                   
 their business.                

46:14.906 --> 46:18.641
              Answering back,   
              just like she did 
              with her father.  

46:18.643 --> 46:22.345
      She said that when        
      Teresa was a little girl, 
      she was pretty feisty.    

46:22.347 --> 46:23.679
           Yeah, I bet she was. 
        (ISABEL CALLING)        

46:23.681 --> 46:24.547
             Teresa!            

46:25.550 --> 46:26.516
             Isabel.            

46:29.053 --> 46:30.019
   (SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE)    

46:30.021 --> 46:31.521
     What a surprise!           

46:32.690 --> 46:33.489
     You look lovely.           

46:34.793 --> 46:35.992
 This is my cousin, Isabel.     

46:36.795 --> 46:38.795
             <i> Hola.</i>             

46:38.797 --> 46:41.430
 What a joy!                    
 Just in time to see            
 my wedding dress.              

46:41.699 --> 46:43.399
            Yes.                

46:43.401 --> 46:46.102
   She's so excited.            
   She's getting married.       

46:46.104 --> 46:47.537
           Oh, congratulations. 
             (SPEAKING SPANISH) 

46:47.539 --> 46:50.039
               What did he say? 
   Congratulations.             

46:51.543 --> 46:53.409
                 Thank you.     

46:53.411 --> 46:54.811
   May I take a picture of you? 
   (SPEAKING SPANISH)           

46:54.813 --> 46:56.379
           A photograph.        

46:56.381 --> 46:57.547
               Yes.             
    Yes?                        

47:02.187 --> 47:04.187
        (CAR ENGINE SPUTTERING) 
      (BEGONA SPEAKING SPANISH) 

47:04.189 --> 47:07.824
       That's uncle's car.      
       It's always broken down. 

47:07.826 --> 47:09.725
 That's my uncle's car.         
 It never works.                

47:09.727 --> 47:11.294
                 HENRY: Really? 

47:11.296 --> 47:14.463
   Well, maybe we can help out. 

47:14.465 --> 47:15.698
                Come on, Marco. 
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

47:15.700 --> 47:17.600
        I'll show you my dress. 

47:17.602 --> 47:19.836
          Automobile repair?    
          I thought you didn't  
          do automobile repair. 

47:19.838 --> 47:20.937
    (HENRY SPEAKING SPANISH)    

47:20.939 --> 47:22.104
   Hello?                       

47:23.441 --> 47:24.674
 Can we give you a hand?        

47:24.676 --> 47:26.108
     (ALL SPEAKING SPANISH)     

47:26.110 --> 47:28.611
                      American? 
  Yes, American.                

47:28.613 --> 47:30.479
              If you want to    
              buy me a new car. 

47:30.481 --> 47:32.481
                  Not good...   

47:32.483 --> 47:34.050
      You wanna get in the car, 
      get ready to start it up? 

47:34.052 --> 47:37.687
 It's the carburetor.           
 It wouldn't happen             
 with a Spanish car.            

47:37.689 --> 47:42.225
        Bad times for everyone. 
        We're better here       
        than in the city.       

47:42.227 --> 47:45.027
            We grow vegetables  
            and exchange things 
            with neighbors.     

47:45.029 --> 47:46.495
            But in Bilbao...    

47:47.832 --> 47:49.532
           All right. Crank it. 

47:51.202 --> 47:53.636
    Oh, no, no, no. No, no, no. 
    Wait, wait. Hold on.        

47:53.638 --> 47:55.004
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

47:55.006 --> 47:57.240
           We need it,          
           our daughter         
           is getting married   

47:57.242 --> 47:59.876
                 and we'll have 
                 to visit her.  

47:59.878 --> 48:02.211
         Or if we have to       
         leave here in a hurry. 

48:04.349 --> 48:07.950
    Is it better to send Begona 
    and my daughter to Bilbao?  

48:07.952 --> 48:10.052
  If I were you,                
  I'd leave as soon             
  as possible.                  

48:11.656 --> 48:12.922
             HENRY: Yeah, okay. 

48:12.924 --> 48:14.156
            Give it another go. 

48:14.158 --> 48:15.324
     (CAR ENGINE STARTING)      

48:16.461 --> 48:17.627
 MARCO: Yes!                    

48:41.986 --> 48:42.919
      (PRAYING IN SPANISH)      

48:43.588 --> 48:44.654
          God, help me!         

49:11.883 --> 49:13.015
                         Why?   

49:15.954 --> 49:17.586
           Why do you insist on 
           breaking the rules?  

49:19.590 --> 49:22.625
         Life is so much easier 
         if you just listen.    

49:23.561 --> 49:24.627
  Please don't do it.           

49:26.497 --> 49:27.730
    I'm innocent.               

49:28.800 --> 49:30.266
    I'm innocent.               

49:34.906 --> 49:36.272
     I've never shot a man.     

49:59.163 --> 50:00.363
 (BREATHING HEAVILY)            

50:11.109 --> 50:12.541
 (GASPING WITH RELIEF)          

50:16.781 --> 50:17.680
           Thank you.           

50:19.283 --> 50:20.082
           Thank you.           
         (COCKING GUN)          

50:21.052 --> 50:22.084
                 (VASYL SHOUTS) 

50:33.031 --> 50:36.365
   Makes me angry               
   to have to do                
   your work, Mikiavich.        

50:37.835 --> 50:40.836
 I asked you to bring me        
 an enemy of the people,        

50:40.838 --> 50:43.105
    and all I get is            
    this fascist pig.           

50:44.776 --> 50:47.643
  And I have to do              
  it all by myself.             

50:48.813 --> 50:50.146
                I understand.   
 No!                            

50:51.883 --> 50:53.883
 Clearly you do not.            

50:53.885 --> 50:56.118
 In Moscow, the party denounces 
 someone every day.             

50:56.120 --> 50:57.520
  Why?                          

50:57.522 --> 51:01.357
 Because it keeps               
 the proletariat in line.       

51:01.359 --> 51:04.427
 You have to do it better,      
 Mikiavich.                     

51:04.429 --> 51:06.962
  Bring me an enemy             
  of the revolution,            

51:06.964 --> 51:09.298
  or some big prize             

51:09.300 --> 51:14.670
 and then we can                
 continue this most             
 enlightening conversation.     

52:18.069 --> 52:19.135
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

52:19.137 --> 52:21.570
                It's Teresa,    
                as a child.     

52:21.572 --> 52:23.139
 HENRY: That's Teresa?          
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

52:23.141 --> 52:26.242
             Her father,        
             a football player. 

52:26.244 --> 52:30.412
        Football!               
        Ferocious, like Teresa. 

52:30.414 --> 52:31.580
    (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)     

52:33.818 --> 52:35.284
 My cousin wants                
 to know the opinion            

52:35.286 --> 52:36.886
 of a famous writer             
 about her dress.               

52:37.755 --> 52:38.621
                          Oh.   

52:40.424 --> 52:41.223
                   (STAMMERING) 
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

52:41.225 --> 52:42.458
     Do you like it?            

52:43.027 --> 52:44.160
            I don't know why... 

52:44.162 --> 52:45.561
       I drew it myself.        

52:45.563 --> 52:46.562
                     Yeah, I... 

52:46.564 --> 52:48.197
 It's at the dressmaker's.      

52:49.534 --> 52:52.301
        My boyfriend            
        hasn't seen it yet,     
        he's at the front.      

52:52.303 --> 52:53.536
  I wanted a man's opinion.     

52:55.940 --> 52:57.806
      Well, I think it's, um... 

52:59.210 --> 53:00.676
                   Very pretty. 

53:02.180 --> 53:03.579
 Really?                        
 Do you think it's pretty?      

53:03.581 --> 53:04.780
                    Yeah, sure. 

53:04.782 --> 53:06.282
             Very, very pretty. 

53:08.653 --> 53:10.486
  Guess I said something right. 

53:10.488 --> 53:13.189
 Come on.                       
 Lunch is ready!                

53:13.191 --> 53:14.423
 Lunch.                         

53:14.425 --> 53:15.591
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

53:15.593 --> 53:17.893
 Yes, we agree                  
 to the plan.                   

53:20.665 --> 53:24.667
       Please, inform Franco    
       that after the operation 

53:24.669 --> 53:27.703
              he must advance   
              quickly to Bilbao 

53:27.705 --> 53:31.140
          or he will miss       
          a golden opportunity. 

53:31.142 --> 53:33.909
           The General always   
           advances slowly,     

53:33.911 --> 53:37.680
            he prefers to shoot 
            his enemies         
            house by house.     

53:37.682 --> 53:41.750
   Yes, but delays              
   cost money.                  

53:41.752 --> 53:44.453
          There's no Republican 
          aviation in the area. 

53:44.455 --> 53:47.423
       They only have           
       one plane in Bilbao      
       and it's being repaired. 

53:47.992 --> 53:49.258
              Splendid.         

53:52.597 --> 53:55.064
 Where's the ten of hearts?     
                Here you are.   

53:55.066 --> 53:56.865
 No, it hasn't come up.         

53:56.867 --> 53:57.800
                  Thank you.    

53:59.036 --> 54:00.436
            MARCO: Fold a card. 

54:01.072 --> 54:01.870
 Perhaps she has it.            

54:02.640 --> 54:03.505
 It's magic.                    

54:04.609 --> 54:05.507
                        (GASPS) 

54:06.043 --> 54:07.977
              No.               

54:07.979 --> 54:08.978
        (ALL EXCLAIMING)        

54:10.147 --> 54:11.714
        You are a big cheat.    

54:12.984 --> 54:14.850
    You two are in it together. 

54:14.852 --> 54:15.818
        He's a big cheater.     

54:15.820 --> 54:16.885
            A toast!            

54:16.887 --> 54:18.187
             Cheers.            

54:18.189 --> 54:20.256
        For the magician!       
        American, cheers!       

54:26.197 --> 54:27.763
       (TUNING ACCORDION)       

54:27.765 --> 54:30.833
 Uncle will play a song.        
 I hope you like it.            

54:30.835 --> 54:34.637
                      Yes!      
         We can dance,          
         if someone teaches me. 

54:35.239 --> 54:36.705
     (PLAYING LIVELY MUSIC)     

54:38.209 --> 54:40.309
                    Can I?      
               Yes.             

54:45.983 --> 54:46.949
    Let's see.                  

54:48.019 --> 54:50.019
    I've no idea.               
                It's very easy. 

55:02.967 --> 55:03.966
             You want to dance? 

55:05.936 --> 55:06.802
 Oh, come on. You can't...      

55:10.574 --> 55:12.941
  You know, I'm                 
  actually a very good dancer.  

55:12.943 --> 55:14.043
        Start like this?        
     (AIRPLANE APPROACHING)     

55:15.546 --> 55:16.645
           Is that one of ours? 

55:17.481 --> 55:18.514
           No.                  

55:19.884 --> 55:20.649
 MARCO: It's German.            

55:21.285 --> 55:22.384
            German.             

55:23.454 --> 55:24.620
        Let's go inside.        

55:28.359 --> 55:29.858
 Isabel!                        
          Isabel!               

55:32.496 --> 55:33.629
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

55:33.631 --> 55:35.064
                    Go, go!     

55:36.334 --> 55:37.333
           (PANTING)            

55:38.035 --> 55:38.934
                     You see.   

56:28.652 --> 56:29.718
 VASYL: Let me be clear.        

56:32.256 --> 56:33.822
   Okay,                        
   I'm not sure I believe this. 

56:35.693 --> 56:38.193
          You invite journalist 
          to your family home,  

56:38.195 --> 56:41.597
    and then the American...    
    He tries to send this, hmm? 

56:42.600 --> 56:44.066
        Maybe he was...         
                Don't lie to... 

56:45.903 --> 56:47.870
          I'm sorry. I'm sorry. 
          Don't lie to me.      

56:48.939 --> 56:50.839
       As I was...              
                   Just...      

56:50.841 --> 56:52.574
  What's happening to you?      
               Just go, okay?   

56:52.576 --> 56:54.410
                  Just go!      

57:11.896 --> 57:13.162
   (INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)   

57:18.269 --> 57:19.034
               Please, come in. 

57:22.106 --> 57:24.173
   I'm sorry, Mr. Howell,       
   but I cannot authorize this. 

57:25.543 --> 57:27.142
      I'm sorry?                

57:27.144 --> 57:29.077
           It says the Republic 
           has lost its morale. 

57:31.715 --> 57:33.715
   You criticized the hospital, 
   and what about               
   the burned girl?             

57:34.885 --> 57:36.485
              You gave her      
              too little space. 

57:37.688 --> 57:40.189
 Well, the article              
 isn't about a burned girl.     

57:40.191 --> 57:42.658
 It's about the horrors of war, 
 and the people                 
 trapped in the middle of it.   

57:43.761 --> 57:44.893
               Well, we are     
               not demoralized. 

57:46.997 --> 57:47.863
     (SCOFFS)                   

57:49.266 --> 57:50.532
 It is true what they say.      

57:52.002 --> 57:56.205
 They use a pretty face         
 to push me to tell the truth.  

57:56.207 --> 57:59.141
 But what you really mean       
 is you want me to              
 push your propaganda.          

57:59.143 --> 58:01.677
 You know,                      
 this whole office is a story!  

58:01.679 --> 58:03.445
 I should send                  
 a photo of you to New York.    

58:03.447 --> 58:04.847
   You're not sending anything. 

58:04.849 --> 58:06.081
   I'll handle this, Teresa.    

58:08.919 --> 58:11.854
 I am not some Italian          
 journalist, you know.          

58:11.856 --> 58:13.822
  I'm the <i> New York</i>             
 <i> Herald Tribune.</i>               

58:13.824 --> 58:16.091
      I know exactly who        
      you are, Mr. Howell.      

58:17.528 --> 58:18.694
 What's that supposed to mean?  

58:21.098 --> 58:22.698
      Why don't you             
      come to Russia, huh?      

58:24.201 --> 58:27.836
 You will be a hero             
 of the revolution,             

58:27.838 --> 58:30.072
           as soon as you       
           put a sheet of paper 
           in a typewriter.     

58:32.910 --> 58:36.278
 In your dreams, comrade.       
                     (CHUCKLES) 

58:37.715 --> 58:39.014
               Don't play tough 
               guy with me.     

58:41.452 --> 58:43.852
       We know you left your    
       interpreter in Ethiopia. 

58:45.789 --> 58:48.190
       The Italians,            
       they came to your hotel, 
       and then what, huh?      

58:49.126 --> 58:49.992
                 Tell me.       

58:51.428 --> 58:52.694
         You ran away.          

58:58.802 --> 59:00.068
                 (YELPS)        
                    TERESA: No! 

59:23.694 --> 59:24.626
       (SPEAKING GERMAN)        

59:24.628 --> 59:26.094
             Gentlemen,         

59:26.096 --> 59:27.329
            thermite!           

59:34.405 --> 59:38.674
         In just a few seconds, 
         it reaches             
         1,000 degrees Celsius. 

59:38.676 --> 59:41.176
 and melts anything             
 it comes into contact with.    

59:43.414 --> 59:45.213
 During the 8 minutes           
 it burns,                      

59:45.215 --> 59:49.251
 it can't be put out            
 with water nor sand.           

59:49.253 --> 59:53.021
 First, we shall bomb           
 their water supply systems,    

59:54.358 --> 59:56.792
    so they cannot              
    put out any fire.           

59:56.794 --> 59:59.828
 Then we'll incinerate          
 everything with thermite.      

59:59.830 --> 01:00:02.164
 German efficiency              
 at its best:                   

01:00:02.166 --> 01:00:05.133
 minimum intervention,          
 maximum destruction!           

01:00:14.445 --> 01:00:16.211
        (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING) 

01:00:43.440 --> 01:00:44.640
                (CLOCK TICKING) 

01:01:10.768 --> 01:01:11.800
   Meeting someone?             

01:01:12.536 --> 01:01:14.236
                            No. 

01:01:14.238 --> 01:01:17.506
 Good.                          
 I need something translated.   

01:01:17.508 --> 01:01:19.574
 I'm afraid                     
 you'll have to stay.           

01:01:19.576 --> 01:01:21.143
    It can't wait               
    until tomorrow morning?     

01:01:26.483 --> 01:01:27.416
        No.                     

01:01:48.906 --> 01:01:50.005
   (INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)    

01:02:27.044 --> 01:02:29.010
             Tired?             

01:02:29.012 --> 01:02:32.214
     I have some pages left,    
     but I can't read any word. 

01:02:32.716 --> 01:02:32.981
                 I'm exhausted. 

01:02:36.920 --> 01:02:39.387
 There's a reception            
 at City Hall tomorrow night.   

01:02:40.991 --> 01:02:42.224
 Will you come with me?         

01:02:43.227 --> 01:02:44.226
     I'll be glad to.           

01:02:55.139 --> 01:02:56.538
   (CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)    

01:03:35.078 --> 01:03:36.111
          VASYL: No, thank you. 

01:03:38.448 --> 01:03:39.381
 Thank you.                     

01:03:48.826 --> 01:03:50.125
 I'm sorry I couldn't meet you. 

01:03:51.728 --> 01:03:53.395
       Vasyl kept me            
       working until very late. 

01:03:54.932 --> 01:03:56.097
               I think he knew. 

01:03:59.770 --> 01:04:00.569
   Is that all?                 

01:04:02.306 --> 01:04:04.706
         You're hurt because I  
         censored your article. 

01:04:04.708 --> 01:04:06.341
 Well, you were the one         
 who wanted me to               
 write the damn thing.          

01:04:06.343 --> 01:04:07.909
         Well, I had no option. 
         I'm sorry.             

01:04:09.479 --> 01:04:10.846
          You don't understand. 

01:04:12.449 --> 01:04:14.216
     Right.                     

01:04:14.218 --> 01:04:16.952
       Henry,                   
       I did love your article. 

01:04:16.954 --> 01:04:18.920
 You must keep writing          
 with the same feeling.         

01:04:20.257 --> 01:04:22.023
 What you are                   
 doing is important.            

01:04:22.025 --> 01:04:23.558
 Not just for Spain,            
 but for you.                   

01:04:24.895 --> 01:04:26.995
 How is it important for Spain  
 if no one gets to read it?     

01:04:26.997 --> 01:04:28.196
 We'll find a way.              

01:04:32.970 --> 01:04:36.071
 Maybe it doesn't make sense,   
 but I was inspired             
 by your writing.               

01:04:45.482 --> 01:04:46.348
              Let's dance.      

01:04:52.689 --> 01:04:54.122
      What's on your mind, hmm? 

01:04:55.025 --> 01:04:57.893
 I don't know, Marta. I...      

01:04:57.895 --> 01:05:01.897
 I don't know how to            
 explain in English,            
 but, you know, this war...     

01:05:02.399 --> 01:05:03.531
        I know this war.        

01:05:03.533 --> 01:05:04.866
 You know...                    

01:05:04.868 --> 01:05:05.634
 Yeah, but tonight's a party... 

01:05:17.848 --> 01:05:20.115
 Communique from your Consul.   

01:05:20.651 --> 01:05:21.449
       Just now.                

01:05:24.254 --> 01:05:26.354
 He says, "Do you have          
 someone for me yet?"           

01:05:26.356 --> 01:05:27.923
         He wants to make       
         an example of someone. 

01:05:28.859 --> 01:05:30.759
           He doesn't care who. 

01:05:30.761 --> 01:05:33.395
          No. He does.          

01:05:44.975 --> 01:05:46.675
           You know I suppose   
           I actually should    
           thank you.           

01:05:49.079 --> 01:05:50.211
          I really liked        
          writing that article. 

01:05:51.014 --> 01:05:52.047
 I liked it a lot.              

01:05:54.151 --> 01:05:55.717
       I need to get back to    
       that sort of writing,    
       and I will.              

01:05:57.220 --> 01:05:58.687
   But perhaps not in Spain.    

01:06:00.757 --> 01:06:01.589
              Are you leaving?  

01:06:03.794 --> 01:06:04.592
    (SCOFFS) Of course you are. 

01:06:10.734 --> 01:06:11.733
             Teresa.            

01:06:14.938 --> 01:06:17.005
 We both want                   
 the same thing, Henry.         

01:06:18.508 --> 01:06:20.575
 The problem is,                
 one of us is not free.         

01:06:41.565 --> 01:06:42.430
                     Teresa.    

01:06:43.533 --> 01:06:44.432
                        Teresa. 

01:06:46.103 --> 01:06:47.268
                     It's late. 

01:06:48.772 --> 01:06:51.206
   There's a foreign delegation 
   coming tomorrow.             

01:06:51.208 --> 01:06:53.074
 I'm sorry, Vasyl,              
 but tomorrow is tomorrow.      

01:07:05.722 --> 01:07:06.554
        (DOOR CREAKING)         

01:07:07.457 --> 01:07:09.057
 Welcome to my hiding place.    

01:07:29.713 --> 01:07:32.047
         This place reminds me  
         of why I do what I do. 

01:07:41.124 --> 01:07:43.825
       Here, we preserve art    
       and beauty from the war. 

01:08:13.557 --> 01:08:15.457
        This place              
        is so emotional for me. 

01:09:34.171 --> 01:09:35.303
       (THUNDER RUMBLING)       

01:09:42.078 --> 01:09:43.243
                      Wait.     

01:09:49.486 --> 01:09:50.818
        I can't.                

01:09:50.819 --> 01:09:51.719
                  Yes, you can. 

01:09:53.657 --> 01:09:54.455
                       Please.  

01:10:09.472 --> 01:10:10.672
 Come with me to Paris.         

01:10:29.559 --> 01:10:30.658
 Good morning, everybody.       

01:10:32.996 --> 01:10:35.096
    Carmen.                     

01:10:35.098 --> 01:10:36.831
 Do you think I can get a line  
 to New York, please?           

01:10:36.833 --> 01:10:37.732
         CARMEN: Okay.          

01:11:08.031 --> 01:11:09.297
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

01:11:09.299 --> 01:11:12.333
          Hold it!              
          Don't move! Hands up! 

01:11:12.335 --> 01:11:14.369
    CONSUL: Your attention.     

01:11:14.371 --> 01:11:18.673
 An official stamp belonging to 
 the censor's                   
 office has been stolen.        

01:11:18.675 --> 01:11:22.477
   All shipment of              
   articles will be suspended   
   until it is recovered.       

01:11:22.479 --> 01:11:23.978
       Search this room.        

01:11:23.980 --> 01:11:25.346
           What? Why?           

01:11:26.716 --> 01:11:28.650
        (CARMEN SPEAKING        
        OTHER LANGUAGE)         

01:11:28.652 --> 01:11:30.718
     Do you know                
     something?                 
                No.             

01:11:32.555 --> 01:11:33.755
    Hey, what are you doing?    

01:11:35.258 --> 01:11:36.057
           (MOUTHING)           

01:11:44.234 --> 01:11:45.933
 This is your coat, Mr. Howell? 

01:11:46.903 --> 01:11:47.735
        (STAMP CLATTERS)        

01:12:06.389 --> 01:12:08.389
              APPROVED          

01:12:17.934 --> 01:12:19.067
   VASYL: Who is                
   the owner of this coat, huh? 

01:12:23.006 --> 01:12:23.905
                         Who?   

01:12:26.776 --> 01:12:27.675
                     It's mine. 

01:12:34.250 --> 01:12:35.450
      Look at the other pocket. 

01:12:36.953 --> 01:12:37.719
              It's my lipstick. 

01:12:48.164 --> 01:12:48.896
   VASYL: What are you doing?   

01:12:50.600 --> 01:12:53.801
          The pin on the lapel, 
          it's also mine.       

01:13:02.078 --> 01:13:04.011
 HENRY: You know                
 that's my coat, Mikiavich.     

01:13:04.013 --> 01:13:04.746
      (TELEPHONE RINGING)       

01:13:05.348 --> 01:13:07.014
 You know it's mine.            

01:13:07.016 --> 01:13:08.449
      Teresa...                 
               I can handle it. 

01:13:09.452 --> 01:13:10.585
             I'll be all right. 

01:13:12.188 --> 01:13:13.388
 You come with me.              

01:13:14.424 --> 01:13:16.124
 No. Where are you taking her?  

01:13:18.795 --> 01:13:20.261
          (COUGHING)            
             (SPEAKING SPANISH) 

01:13:20.263 --> 01:13:22.430
   You're wrong.                

01:13:22.432 --> 01:13:25.600
 This is not a game, Teresa.    
 Do you understand?             
 Do you understand?             

01:13:33.543 --> 01:13:34.742
        (VON RICHTHOFEN         
        SPEAKING GERMAN)        

01:13:34.744 --> 01:13:37.879
      The sacrifices            
      we've made in Spain,      

01:13:37.881 --> 01:13:41.149
      the savings on            
      ammunition and fuel       

01:13:41.151 --> 01:13:42.583
       have not been in vain.   

01:13:43.119 --> 01:13:45.486
                Blitzkrieg      

01:13:45.488 --> 01:13:47.855
           They've been talking 
           about it in Berlin   
           for months.          

01:13:47.857 --> 01:13:52.493
           A three-day air raid 
           carried out in       
           just one afternoon.  

01:13:52.495 --> 01:13:54.896
          As fast as lightning. 

01:13:54.898 --> 01:13:58.399
          We've received orders 
          to put into practice  

01:13:58.401 --> 01:14:00.168
       during our attack today. 

01:14:01.070 --> 01:14:02.470
        Therefore, gentlemen... 

01:14:03.540 --> 01:14:05.440
           enjoy your flight... 

01:14:07.143 --> 01:14:07.909
           to Gernika.          

01:14:11.714 --> 01:14:13.347
 HENRY: Where is Teresa?        

01:14:13.349 --> 01:14:15.183
 I don't have that information. 

01:14:15.185 --> 01:14:16.217
        You liar!               

01:14:21.791 --> 01:14:24.025
      What happens in her life  
      is no longer my business. 

01:14:27.263 --> 01:14:30.031
            Now get out.        
            And take your coat. 

01:14:34.471 --> 01:14:36.637
                    Get out.    

01:14:46.649 --> 01:14:47.682
      Carmen.                   

01:14:51.254 --> 01:14:52.053
 Where is Teresa?               

01:14:53.122 --> 01:14:53.955
                  I don't know. 

01:14:55.492 --> 01:14:56.557
             How should I know? 

01:14:58.194 --> 01:14:59.293
 You're her friend, aren't you? 

01:14:59.295 --> 01:15:00.094
         I don't know anything! 

01:15:01.965 --> 01:15:03.998
       Go away. Leave me alone. 

01:15:04.601 --> 01:15:05.633
      Please!                   

01:15:08.404 --> 01:15:09.270
     Help me.                   

01:15:14.344 --> 01:15:15.109
              Don't you get it? 

01:15:16.346 --> 01:15:20.281
         For God's sake, leave. 

01:15:22.185 --> 01:15:23.017
                  Please.       

01:15:42.238 --> 01:15:43.037
                  MARCO: Henry. 

01:15:44.507 --> 01:15:46.307
               Bad news.        

01:15:46.309 --> 01:15:48.276
       They found the body of   
       that Spanish journalist. 

01:15:48.278 --> 01:15:50.444
 MARCO: My contacts say         
 Teresa didn't leave.           

01:15:50.446 --> 01:15:51.712
 She's in a cheka.              

01:15:51.714 --> 01:15:53.915
            A what?             
                 Soviet prison. 

01:15:53.917 --> 01:15:55.416
       They use it to make      
       their enemies disappear. 

01:15:55.418 --> 01:15:56.384
 It is in Gernika.              

01:15:56.386 --> 01:15:57.285
        Let's go.               

01:16:02.158 --> 01:16:03.124
     (VEHICLE APPROACHING)      

01:16:12.335 --> 01:16:14.969
         She was working        
         right under your nose, 
         was she?               

01:16:14.971 --> 01:16:17.204
     Excellent work, Mikiavich. 
     Stalin will be pleased.    

01:16:17.774 --> 01:16:19.273
        And?                    

01:16:19.275 --> 01:16:20.341
           And what, Mikiavich? 

01:16:22.045 --> 01:16:23.978
 I delivered you                
 an enemy of the people.        

01:16:26.382 --> 01:16:28.649
 My brother, Nikolai.           

01:16:29.352 --> 01:16:30.651
                 Unfortunately, 

01:16:34.057 --> 01:16:34.889
                      too late. 

01:16:36.392 --> 01:16:39.093
            I will need your... 

01:16:39.095 --> 01:16:41.762
     I will need your signature 
     on the death certificate.  

01:16:41.764 --> 01:16:44.098
       Stalin does not forgive, 
       Mikiavich.               

01:16:45.501 --> 01:16:49.403
        You continue your work, 
        or you will have to     
        come back to Moscow,    

01:16:49.405 --> 01:16:51.172
        with some explanations. 

01:17:00.249 --> 01:17:01.349
       (SPEAKING GERMAN)        

01:17:01.351 --> 01:17:03.317
       A magnificent day.       

01:17:03.319 --> 01:17:06.954
          Ideal for a drive     
          along the beach,      
          don't you think?      

01:17:55.204 --> 01:17:56.303
    Good luck, boys!            

01:17:57.240 --> 01:17:58.005
     Everything will be OK!     

01:18:02.311 --> 01:18:03.744
                No, no, no.     

01:18:04.380 --> 01:18:05.279
                Please.         

01:18:06.549 --> 01:18:08.115
 Can you stop this?             

01:18:08.117 --> 01:18:09.283
  We have to follow the orders. 

01:18:13.790 --> 01:18:14.789
   (SOLDIER SPEAKING SPANISH)   

01:18:14.791 --> 01:18:16.290
 Take your clothes off!         

01:18:17.460 --> 01:18:19.960
                          No.   
               Undress!         

01:18:22.398 --> 01:18:23.864
 Vasyl, why are you doing this? 

01:18:26.703 --> 01:18:28.102
     (OPERA MUSIC PLAYING)      
   (TERESA BREATHING HEAVILY)   

01:18:30.273 --> 01:18:31.272
         Vasyl!                 

01:18:34.444 --> 01:18:35.976
                 (CRYING)       

01:18:46.222 --> 01:18:47.788
            Have mercy, please! 

01:18:48.591 --> 01:18:49.457
                 (SOBBING)      

01:18:52.328 --> 01:18:53.761
                    (SCREAMING) 

01:19:13.916 --> 01:19:14.949
         (DOG BARKING)          

01:19:34.837 --> 01:19:36.003
            (CHICKENS CLUCKING) 

01:19:37.340 --> 01:19:38.239
         Out of the way!        

01:19:47.850 --> 01:19:49.350
   (INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)   
      (FOLK MUSIC PLAYING)      

01:19:53.823 --> 01:19:55.122
      (CHILDREN LAUGHING)       

01:20:14.610 --> 01:20:16.043
    (WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH)    

01:20:16.045 --> 01:20:17.278
      It's lovely,              
      how much is it?           

01:20:20.716 --> 01:20:22.616
      Yeah, this is the street. 
      Don Tello Street.         

01:20:22.618 --> 01:20:23.517
               Don Tello, okay. 

01:20:26.055 --> 01:20:27.154
     Excuse me. Excuse me.      

01:20:27.924 --> 01:20:29.323
        Calle Don Tello?        

01:20:30.326 --> 01:20:31.225
        Marco, this way.        

01:20:32.094 --> 01:20:33.360
   (TERESA BREATHING SHAKILY)   

01:20:45.975 --> 01:20:47.374
 Now, don't make                
 this more difficult.           

01:20:49.745 --> 01:20:50.611
     Please.                    

01:20:52.081 --> 01:20:53.314
  Just sign it.                 

01:20:57.553 --> 01:21:00.287
 "I, Teresa Azcotia,            

01:21:01.724 --> 01:21:03.190
 "confess that I'm a traitor,   

01:21:08.231 --> 01:21:10.231
 "and that I sabotaged          
 the revolution."               

01:21:13.669 --> 01:21:15.002
                (TERESA CRYING) 

01:21:15.872 --> 01:21:17.004
 Please.                        

01:21:18.908 --> 01:21:20.574
 Please. Please.                

01:21:23.679 --> 01:21:25.246
       This can't be happening. 

01:21:25.248 --> 01:21:26.981
 I'm sorry.                     

01:21:26.983 --> 01:21:29.049
       This can't be happening. 

01:21:29.051 --> 01:21:31.018
 I'm so sorry. I'm sorry.       

01:21:43.966 --> 01:21:45.199
           (RINGING)            

01:21:50.439 --> 01:21:51.505
            You ask this woman. 

01:21:52.341 --> 01:21:53.274
        Excuse me, sir.         

01:21:54.644 --> 01:21:57.077
         I don't speak Spanish. 
         I need to find         
         Calle Don Tello.       

01:21:57.079 --> 01:21:58.579
         You know what that is? 
    (AIR RAID SIREN BLARING)    

01:21:58.581 --> 01:21:59.580
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

01:21:59.582 --> 01:22:00.514
        We have to go           
        to the shelter!         
        Come on!                

01:22:01.384 --> 01:22:02.249
 Henry, come on.                

01:22:02.852 --> 01:22:04.718
 Henry, come on!                

01:22:04.720 --> 01:22:06.687
         I'm gonna go this way. 
         I'll meet you here     
         in an hour, okay?      

01:22:06.689 --> 01:22:07.554
                 In an hour!    

01:22:10.393 --> 01:22:11.525
   (SIREN CONTINUES BLARING)    

01:22:17.033 --> 01:22:18.232
 (ALL SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE)  

01:22:18.234 --> 01:22:20.067
  Isabel!                       
  Where are you going?          

01:22:20.069 --> 01:22:21.435
               To the tailor's! 

01:22:21.437 --> 01:22:24.438
   Have you gone mad?           
              My wedding dress! 

01:22:24.440 --> 01:22:25.940
 Come back!                     

01:22:26.409 --> 01:22:27.408
            Isabel!             

01:22:30.680 --> 01:22:31.845
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

01:22:31.847 --> 01:22:35.616
   Planes!                      
   Get to the shelter! Come on! 

01:22:35.618 --> 01:22:37.117
             To the shelter!    

01:22:37.119 --> 01:22:38.419
      (PANICKED SCREAMING)      

01:22:38.421 --> 01:22:39.687
 To the shelter!                
 Come on!                       

01:22:43.292 --> 01:22:44.325
             Quickly!           

01:22:50.533 --> 01:22:52.166
     (GRAMOPHONE SKIPPING)      

01:22:53.269 --> 01:22:55.636
 Let's go to the bomb shelter.  
 Take him!                      

01:22:55.638 --> 01:22:58.706
           No, no, no!          

01:22:58.708 --> 01:23:00.007
                     (SOBBING)  

01:23:00.009 --> 01:23:01.575
   (OPERATIC MUSIC SKIPPING)    

01:23:14.023 --> 01:23:15.289
       (PEOPLE SCREAMING)       

01:23:18.160 --> 01:23:19.360
       (CAR HONKING HORN)       

01:23:22.565 --> 01:23:24.198
            Come on!            
            Hurry up!           

01:23:38.514 --> 01:23:40.781
          To the bomb shelter!  
          Hurry up!             

01:23:42.118 --> 01:23:43.717
             Come on!           

01:23:43.719 --> 01:23:45.052
        To the City Hall!       

01:23:46.389 --> 01:23:48.455
             To the shelter!    
             Come on!           

01:23:50.026 --> 01:23:53.127
   Leave that!                  
   Go to the City Hall shelter. 

01:23:53.129 --> 01:23:54.261
              My car!           

01:24:04.640 --> 01:24:05.672
                    Hurry up!   

01:24:10.379 --> 01:24:12.746
 Marta, we have to go.          

01:24:13.182 --> 01:24:14.314
                      Yeah.     

01:24:14.884 --> 01:24:16.417
        Okay. Wait, one second. 

01:24:16.419 --> 01:24:19.386
      One second. Okay... Okay. 

01:24:24.994 --> 01:24:26.527
                (WHIMPERING)    

01:24:37.073 --> 01:24:38.772
                    Isabel!     

01:24:38.774 --> 01:24:40.107
           I'm looking for      
           your cousin, Teresa. 

01:24:40.109 --> 01:24:41.175
            Henry...            
               Calle Don Tello. 

01:24:41.177 --> 01:24:42.676
     -I need your help.         
     -Over there!               

01:24:42.678 --> 01:24:43.577
    This way?                   

01:24:46.115 --> 01:24:47.448
              (GASPS)           

01:24:48.851 --> 01:24:50.250
  No, no, no, no. No, Isabel.   
              No.               

01:24:50.252 --> 01:24:51.118
 No, you can't!                 
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

01:24:51.120 --> 01:24:53.153
            My dress!           
            It's my dress!      

01:24:53.823 --> 01:24:55.823
 Help me.                       

01:24:55.825 --> 01:24:56.824
     Help, I've no strength!    

01:25:08.104 --> 01:25:09.369
    Are you okay? Are you okay? 

01:25:20.049 --> 01:25:21.815
                  Teresa.       

01:25:21.817 --> 01:25:24.618
           Isabel, you have to  
           help me find Teresa. 
        Teresa.                 

01:25:25.121 --> 01:25:26.186
                     Teresa!    

01:25:27.056 --> 01:25:28.288
   Teresa. (SPEAKING SPANISH)   

01:25:28.290 --> 01:25:30.624
    Teresa.                     
    Yes, come on, let's go.     

01:25:32.161 --> 01:25:33.360
    (EXPLOSIONS IN DISTANCE)    

01:25:33.362 --> 01:25:34.428
 (OPERATIC MUSIC PLAYING)       

01:25:34.430 --> 01:25:35.796
               (TERESA SOBBING) 

01:25:48.110 --> 01:25:49.042
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

01:25:49.044 --> 01:25:51.178
             Bastards!          

01:25:51.180 --> 01:25:53.680
              Bastards!         

01:26:01.557 --> 01:26:02.723
           (COUGHING)           

01:26:02.724 --> 01:26:03.890
 Come on,                       
 let's go to the shelter.       

01:26:06.362 --> 01:26:09.930
              I need to find    
              Calle Don Tello.  
              Calle Don Tello.  

01:26:09.932 --> 01:26:11.899
       Cheka?                   
            Go with him!        

01:26:12.801 --> 01:26:14.168
         Young lady, don't!     

01:26:14.170 --> 01:26:15.269
      Stay here! Stay here!     

01:26:15.271 --> 01:26:16.570
             Isabel?            

01:26:25.314 --> 01:26:26.580
 Let's go.                      

01:26:29.919 --> 01:26:30.918
            I have to go back.  

01:26:36.692 --> 01:26:37.875
       (MAN SPEAKING            
       ITALIAN ON RADIO)        

01:26:37.876 --> 01:26:39.059
    The Italian Legionary       
    Air Force awaits orders.    

01:26:39.061 --> 01:26:41.328
          The three Italian SMs 
          are awaiting orders.  

01:26:41.330 --> 01:26:42.663
 This way!                      

01:26:43.732 --> 01:26:45.866
     Freeze!                    
     This is a restricted area! 

01:26:45.868 --> 01:26:47.534
 Open the damn door!            
 The mayor sent us!             

01:26:47.536 --> 01:26:49.036
   You've no jurisdiction here! 

01:26:49.038 --> 01:26:50.103
 Open the fucking door!         

01:26:50.105 --> 01:26:50.938
           (SHOUTING)           

01:26:57.279 --> 01:26:58.745
 Open the door!                 

01:26:58.747 --> 01:26:59.813
    (AIR RAID SIREN BLARING)    

01:27:15.197 --> 01:27:16.129
   (SOLDIER SPEAKING SPANISH)   

01:27:16.131 --> 01:27:17.297
       Stop!                    

01:27:18.167 --> 01:27:19.666
 Why are you here?              

01:27:19.668 --> 01:27:20.734
              Okay.             

01:27:20.736 --> 01:27:22.035
  Get out!                      
  Get out!                      

01:27:22.037 --> 01:27:23.270
           Just calm down.      

01:27:23.272 --> 01:27:24.371
 Drop the gun, boy!             
                       Drop it. 

01:27:24.373 --> 01:27:26.607
 I have orders to shoot!        

01:27:26.609 --> 01:27:27.341
              Put the gun down. 
   (PANTING)                    

01:27:28.143 --> 01:27:29.276
                        Okay.   

01:27:34.783 --> 01:27:35.816
            Teresa!             
  (PRISONERS SPEAKING SPANISH)  

01:27:35.818 --> 01:27:36.850
              Help!             

01:27:38.053 --> 01:27:39.686
                  Help! Please! 

01:27:41.457 --> 01:27:43.724
 Open the door, please!         
 Help!                          

01:27:43.726 --> 01:27:46.260
 Let us out!                    
 Let us out, please!            

01:27:46.862 --> 01:27:48.862
 Please, let us out.            

01:27:48.864 --> 01:27:50.464
        Teresa. Teresa!         

01:27:50.466 --> 01:27:51.932
              Get the keys!     
              On the wall!      

01:27:51.934 --> 01:27:53.433
 Get the keys! Get the keys!    

01:27:57.906 --> 01:27:59.473
                    Get out!    

01:28:00.142 --> 01:28:01.875
 Come on, let's go!             

01:28:02.811 --> 01:28:03.910
         Teresa!                

01:28:06.715 --> 01:28:08.949
             Henry.             

01:28:08.951 --> 01:28:10.584
            Teresa!             
       TERESA: (MUFFLED) Henry! 

01:28:10.953 --> 01:28:12.019
            Teresa!             

01:28:13.989 --> 01:28:14.721
               (TERESA SOBBING) 

01:28:15.124 --> 01:28:15.989
                      Okay.     

01:28:17.192 --> 01:28:19.593
          I got you. I got you. 

01:28:22.898 --> 01:28:24.064
          Henry.                

01:28:24.867 --> 01:28:26.433
 Don't leave me alone.          

01:28:26.435 --> 01:28:28.335
            Never. Never.       

01:29:07.376 --> 01:29:09.042
       There's a step.          
       There's a step.          
       There, there.            

01:29:09.912 --> 01:29:10.811
           This way.            

01:29:19.254 --> 01:29:20.554
         Shit.                  

01:29:30.232 --> 01:29:31.598
   (WOMAN CRYING IN DISTANCE)   

01:29:55.591 --> 01:29:57.190
    (AIR RAID SIREN BLARING)    
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

01:29:57.192 --> 01:29:58.458
               Planes again!    

01:30:00.996 --> 01:30:03.063
              Murderers!        
 Run, they're coming back!      

01:30:23.719 --> 01:30:25.185
      (PANICKED SCREAMING)      

01:30:28.724 --> 01:30:29.723
                         Help!  

01:30:30.859 --> 01:30:31.758
                 Open the door! 

01:30:32.428 --> 01:30:33.760
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

01:30:33.762 --> 01:30:36.797
                   Open up!     
 You can't come in, it's full.  

01:30:36.799 --> 01:30:38.899
       You can't come in.       
       You can't come in.       

01:30:40.002 --> 01:30:41.201
 (TERESA PANTING)               

01:30:48.243 --> 01:30:50.811
         Have you seen my mum?  
     Don't worry. She's coming. 

01:30:50.813 --> 01:30:52.579
              And my dad?       
              Yes, don't worry. 

01:30:52.581 --> 01:30:53.580
          (EXPLOSION)           

01:30:55.250 --> 01:30:57.050
      My God!                   
 It hurts.                      

01:30:57.052 --> 01:31:00.253
 Don't worry, calm down.        
 Look.                          

01:31:00.255 --> 01:31:04.090
 Bite this, okay?               
 Bite it hard so your           
 eardrums don't burst.          

01:31:04.092 --> 01:31:06.526
 I've got enough for everyone.  
 Bite it.                       

01:31:07.729 --> 01:31:10.497
 Bite it hard.                  
 Good, bite it.                 

01:31:10.499 --> 01:31:12.532
 Little guy!                    
 Bite it, that's it, hard!      

01:31:16.572 --> 01:31:19.706
         And for me?            
              Wait, I think     
              I've got another. 

01:31:19.708 --> 01:31:22.108
 Will this do?                  
                  Yes, perfect. 

01:31:22.110 --> 01:31:23.877
          Thank you.            
           There, bite it hard. 

01:31:30.419 --> 01:31:32.085
                    Teresa!     

01:31:36.758 --> 01:31:38.258
    Teresa!                     

01:31:50.873 --> 01:31:52.038
       (BANGING ON DOOR)        

01:31:57.312 --> 01:31:58.111
          (DOOR OPENS)          

01:32:04.152 --> 01:32:05.252
        (ALL MURMURING)         

01:32:11.760 --> 01:32:13.193
             Go with your side. 

01:32:31.146 --> 01:32:32.913
 Sit down.                      

01:32:55.203 --> 01:32:56.036
        (ALL SCREAMING)         

01:32:58.740 --> 01:32:59.773
        (ROOF CREAKING)         

01:33:06.315 --> 01:33:07.280
        Teresa.                 

01:33:09.017 --> 01:33:10.717
 Teresa,                        
 I need you to listen to me.    

01:33:10.719 --> 01:33:12.085
 We have to get out of here.    

01:33:12.087 --> 01:33:13.587
  It's too dangerous out there. 

01:33:13.589 --> 01:33:16.823
    This ceiling could          
    collapse at any moment.     

01:33:16.825 --> 01:33:19.626
   If we're gonna die,          
   let's at least               
   die in the light.            

01:33:23.632 --> 01:33:24.798
        Come on.                

01:33:35.344 --> 01:33:36.610
         (BABY CRYING)          

01:33:47.789 --> 01:33:48.922
       (SPEAKING SPANISH)       

01:33:48.924 --> 01:33:51.424
                Don't look.     
                Shut your eyes. 

01:33:51.426 --> 01:33:54.361
         What happened to them? 
       Nothing, they're asleep. 

01:34:04.006 --> 01:34:06.640
           HENRY: Marco! Marta! 
           We have to get       
           out of this city.    

01:34:06.642 --> 01:34:08.708
 Come on. Go! Go, go, go!       

01:34:12.481 --> 01:34:13.279
                  MARCO: Marta. 

01:34:17.386 --> 01:34:18.351
 This way. This way.            

01:34:24.960 --> 01:34:25.859
                Come on!        

01:34:31.733 --> 01:34:32.699
              (WOMAN SCREAMING) 

01:34:51.420 --> 01:34:52.852
      HENRY: Come on. Hurry up! 

01:34:59.294 --> 01:35:00.326
    (CHILD SPEAKING SPANISH)    

01:35:00.328 --> 01:35:01.728
   Help!                        

01:35:04.666 --> 01:35:05.965
            Come on!            

01:35:20.582 --> 01:35:21.448
       (TERESA COUGHING)        

01:35:28.690 --> 01:35:32.726
 Teresa, are you all right?     

01:35:34.396 --> 01:35:35.395
 (GROANING) We                  
 have to keep going.            

01:35:39.568 --> 01:35:40.800
              (TERESA GROANING) 

01:35:42.971 --> 01:35:45.071
      Yeah. I'm okay. I'm okay. 

01:35:49.978 --> 01:35:53.480
      Henry, are you all right? 

01:36:11.566 --> 01:36:13.166
  Promise me you won't give up. 

01:36:13.168 --> 01:36:14.834
 Don't speak.                   
 Just save your energy.         

01:36:15.270 --> 01:36:16.136
                  Oh!           

01:36:16.772 --> 01:36:19.038
             Okay, I got you.   

01:36:19.040 --> 01:36:21.508
   All right,                   
   I'm gonna pick you up. Okay? 

01:36:21.510 --> 01:36:22.842
      I'm gonna carry you.      

01:36:32.154 --> 01:36:34.387
      TERESA:                   
      You'll follow your heart? 

01:36:35.423 --> 01:36:37.490
        I will. I will.         

01:36:39.795 --> 01:36:42.462
   Tell the story to the world. 

01:36:42.464 --> 01:36:43.296
                  MARCO: Henry. 

01:36:44.633 --> 01:36:45.965
    (MARCO SPEAKING SPANISH)    

01:36:46.601 --> 01:36:48.034
    We need help.               

01:36:57.712 --> 01:36:58.745
             (SPEAKING SPANISH) 

01:36:58.747 --> 01:36:59.579
                       Sorry.   

01:37:03.185 --> 01:37:05.952
      There's nothing I can do. 
      I'm so sorry.             

01:37:07.656 --> 01:37:08.888
        (HENRY SOBBING)         

01:37:53.935 --> 01:37:55.435
    They will take care of her. 

01:37:58.940 --> 01:38:00.240
   (CONTINUES SOBBING)          

01:38:05.380 --> 01:38:07.180
 Henry. Henry.                  

01:38:53.795 --> 01:38:55.295
         (SOBBING)              

01:39:33.034 --> 01:39:34.434
         (WOMEN CRYING)         

01:40:01.663 --> 01:40:02.595
     (VEHICLE APPROACHING)      

01:40:11.573 --> 01:40:12.638
 PIERRE: Are you fine?          

01:40:15.176 --> 01:40:17.143
 I heard on the radio.          

01:40:19.748 --> 01:40:21.647
          I need you to take us 
          to the Press Office.  

01:40:23.084 --> 01:40:25.218
 Yes. Yes. Come on.             

01:40:38.933 --> 01:40:40.233
                You have to go. 

01:40:40.235 --> 01:40:41.401
    What are you doing?         

01:40:47.075 --> 01:40:48.074
                  I don't know. 

01:40:50.078 --> 01:40:51.144
                      Go.       
       (ENGINE STARTING)        

01:41:02.190 --> 01:41:03.790
      (CRYING)                  

01:41:24.179 --> 01:41:25.311
     (MAN SPEAKING SPANISH)     

01:41:25.313 --> 01:41:26.746
                Stop!           

01:41:26.748 --> 01:41:27.580
        (COCKING RIFLE)         

01:41:34.089 --> 01:41:36.322
 Don't move!                    

01:41:36.324 --> 01:41:38.424
  One more step                 
  and I'll shoot.               

01:41:49.370 --> 01:41:51.671
     I need a line to New York. 

01:41:56.644 --> 01:41:57.743
             (SPEAKING SPANISH) 

01:41:57.745 --> 01:41:59.278
            Whatever they need. 

01:42:12.193 --> 01:42:13.192
               (SNIFFLES)       

01:42:25.140 --> 01:42:26.339
       Listen, George.          

01:42:27.976 --> 01:42:30.476
  Here's your damn war story.   

01:42:32.113 --> 01:42:35.481
    Twenty-six April, 1937.     
    Gernika.                    

01:42:37.051 --> 01:42:38.718
       Don't give a damn        
       if you use my name       

01:42:38.720 --> 01:42:40.653
     or you have                
     someone else sign it.      

01:42:40.655 --> 01:42:43.456
   But it's                     
   the story I want printed.    

01:42:43.458 --> 01:42:44.624
             Ready?             

01:42:47.862 --> 01:42:50.897
     A very small town          
     in the north of Spain      

01:42:50.899 --> 01:42:52.932
      is about to               
      become very famous,       

01:42:54.169 --> 01:42:55.935
 but for all the wrong reasons. 
